messages.content: I am emailing them and telling them we’re planning on releasing around 8:30 tonight and to let me know if they have any opposition to that. They shouldn’t.
I told them I’ll send one more email tonight once it is live and fully published
ok so what is the communication to Bell team?

Could we shoot for about 830 tonight? I’ll be home then and can make sure to be on and test it once you publish.

That should give Bell time to be out if they are in it right now too.
Isaac Carpenter certification is complete, when would you like to publish?
Once it’s released to Prod, I will get in and check in their live database before I email them and tell them it’s all good to go.

It was tested in Preview Edition qadb, which is technically BLN data, but not there specific one, no.

 

Neal created one in Production, I created one, and then I also confirmed it was an issue in Preview Edition before Eric pushed the fix to QADB, and now it's working, so I'm pretty confident that it got it.

It was tested in Preview Edition qadb, which is technically BLN data, but not there specific one, no.

 

Neal created one in Production, I created one, and then I also confirmed it was an issue in Preview Edition before Eric pushed the fix to QADB, and now it's working, so I'm pretty confident that it got it.
Isaac Carpenter was this tested against their scenario or just a new general one?

Yes I am very confident this works, and both fixes for the Bulk update and the Retail NY$ update the corresponding columns immediately. 

 

I have not, but I will get ready to write them an email that we have a fix and verified it works in testing, and are waiting on the store to approve us.
Isaac have you communicated anything else to these guys?
so we are 100 % sure this corrects both the old and new issue as well as for changes to unit ST and $ ST?
it's already in certification but i'll let you know when it is ready to publish

I think we should be good to go ahead and submit to the store. 

 

I will keep testing a bit to be safe but pretty confident everything is fully working now.

 

Keep me updated on the store submission process so I can keep Bell in the loop.
Yep, you're right, been a while haha, but updating those values both single cell and bulk update there work and all math's out.

changing retailny will only change the ForecastSales and ForecastShips (these are usually hidden in the column chooser initially), but not the ForecastShipUnits or ForecastSalesUnits. make sure you're looking at the correct fields for that one

The bulk update all looks good to me. 

 

The only thing is changing the Retail NY doesn't update the Ships or Sales. I honestly don't know what to expect those values to update to when I change the price. It may be good to go, but I know you mentioned updating it, but single cell or bulk update or Retail NY is not doing anything to Forecast ships or Forecast sales.
Okay cool, I'll close the old one then
